<chapter xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"  xml:id="chapter-linear-equations-and-inequalities">
  <title>Linear</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
      This chapter is all about <q>linear</q> math expressions. Without getting into the weeds, an
      example of a linear math expression is <m>2x+5</m>. A linear expression like this could come
      out of a word problem, be on one side of an equation like <m>2x+5=7</m>, be part of a function
      formula like <m>f(x)=2x+5</m>, be part of an equation to graph such as <m>y=2x+5</m>, and much
      more.
    </p>
